    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>That double <code>**</code> tells Gulp to look <em>recursively</em> inside the <code>sass</code> directory
for <code>.scss</code> files. That'll let me create subdirectories later if I want.</p>
<p>Now that we've loaded the files, we'll just pipe them through whatever we
need. Use <code>pipe()</code> then <code>sass()</code> inside of it. Gulp works with streams, so
imagine Gulp is opening up all of our <code>.scss</code> files as a big stream and then
passing them one-by-one through the <code>pipe()</code> function. So at this point,
all that Sass has been processed. Then finally, we'll pipe that to <code>gulp.dest()</code>
and say: "Hey, I want you to dump the finished product to the <code>web/css/</code>
directory.":</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="78b40e208e">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            
            9 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="gulpfile.js">gulpfile.js</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="1"></td>
            <td class="blob-code"><span class="hljs-keyword">var</span> gulp = <span class="hljs-built_in">require</span>(<span class="hljs-string">'gulp'</span>);</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="2"></td>
            <td class="blob-code"><span class="hljs-keyword">var</span> sass = <span class="hljs-built_in">require</span>(<span class="hljs-string">'gulp-sass'</span>);</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="3"></td>
            <td class="blob-code"></td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
