                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="8"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">});</td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>That's all we need! Head back to the terminal and just type <code>gulp</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">gulp</div></code></pre>
<p>Ok, no errors - that seems good. But now we <em>do</em> have a <code>web/css/styles.css</code>
file. And I know it got processed through Sass because the original is using
a variable.</p>
<h2 id="using-the-boring-css-file">Using the Boring CSS File <a class="headerlink" href="sass#using-the-boring-css-file" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
